<title>Audio.Stop Function</title>

<subheader>Format</subheader>

<logicsyntax audio>
d = audio_name.stop();
</logicsyntax>


<subheader>Description</subheader>

The <logiccolor audio>audio.stop</logiccolor> function ends the background recording session for an <link audio.hgt>audio</link> object. Background recording is started with the function <logiccolor audio>audio.record</logiccolor>. The call to <logiccolor audio>audio.stop</logiccolor> should be made to finish the recording session started with <logiccolor audio>audio.record</logiccolor>. This function is <b>not</b> used for interactive recording with <logiccolor audio>audio.recordInteractive</logiccolor>.


<subheader>Return Value</subheader>

The function returns the duration of the recorded audio in seconds (and fractional seconds) or DEFAULT if the audio failed to record.


